{{SameNameNote|ACS|ZScript|DropInventory (ZScript)}}
__NOTOC__ void '''DropInventory''' (int ''tid'', str ''itemtodrop'');
==Usage== Drops to the ground the specified [[item]] from the inventory of the actor or actors with the matching {{c|[[TID|tid]]}}. The item has to be present in the inventory in order for it to be dropped. With each call of the function, only one sample of the specified item is dropped.
If ''tid'' is 0, the item is dropped from the script activator's inventory.
===Parameters=== *''tid'': the {{c|tid}} of the actor or actors from which the item is to be dropped. *''itemtodrop'': the item to be dropped.
== Examples == This script will drop a {{Class|shotgun}} from the activator of the script, provided that the activator has a shotgun in their inventory, of course.
Script 1 (void) { [[DropInventory]](0, "{{Class|Shotgun}}"); }
== See also == * [[A_DropInventory]] [[category:ACS Inventory functions]]
